\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\cf1\striked0\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\hich\af2\dbch\af2\afs22\ai0\ab0\langfe1033\lang1033\loch\f2\fs22\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \cf1\ulnone\ulc0 \u9632\'3f\tab}\ilvl2\ls1 \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-180\tx2520\li2520\ri0\lin2520\rin0\fi-180{\lang1025\rtlch \ltrch\loch
A focus on sheer performance rather than appearance or manufacturability in the early stages.  In fact sometimes noise is considered beneficial because people perceive something that\'92s louder to be more powerful. Obviously dispensing with that kind of pandering to ignorance is an easy way to make progress on performance.  I also rejected the idea that it must be cheap.  The *ratio* of cost to performance is much more important.  In a way both of these and much more comes to making a wise objective function early on and allowing that to guide development efforts.  The whole thing is one big optimization effort.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\cf1\striked0\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\hich\af2\dbch\af2\afs22\ai0\ab0\langfe1033\lang1033\loch\f2\fs22\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \cf1\ulnone\ulc0 \u9675\'3f\tab}\ilvl1\ls1 \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-360\tx1800\li1800\ri0\lin1800\rin0\fi-360{\lang1025\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The methods I have employed including optimization, actually building prototypes, working with good efficiency are important.  Both in terms of getting on with things faster and sooner and also with less money and space.  With a fixed budget, higher efficiency will give a better result.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\cf1\striked0\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\hich\af2\dbch\af2\afs22\ai0\ab0\langfe1033\lang1033\loch\f2\fs22\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \cf1\ulnone\ulc0 \u9632\'3f\tab}\ilvl2\ls1 \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-180\tx2520\li2520\ri0\lin2520\rin0\fi-180{\lang1025\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Prove the most uncertain stuff first.  That was the blades and then the ability to print them with reasonable efficiency.  Then the motor/driver comes after.  That way if you have to change course you have less lost effort.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\sl276\slmult1\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\sb0\sa0\ltrpar\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\cf1\striked0\i0\ulnone\ulc0\b0\hich\af2\dbch\af2\afs22\ai0\ab0\langfe1033\lang1033\loch\f2\fs22\lang1033{\listtext\pard\plain \cf1\ulnone\ulc0 \u9632\'3f\tab}\ilvl2\ls1 \li360\ri0\lin360\rin0\fi-180\tx2520\li2520\ri0\lin2520\rin0\fi-180{\lang1025\rtlch \ltrch\loch
