Keep orderly notes and data, I don\'92t think paper notes are really up to the challenge.  You can\'92t make a spreadsheet on paper.  This is important to remember and refer to what worked best, so you can mix and match the best features during the optimization process.  And also if something goes wrong you can figure it out better.}
