One thing that has some potential is airfoil shaped blades, i.e. the back of the blade has a different curvature than the front.  This would be easy to do with printing but it makes the blade thick so with molding you\'92d end up with heavy blades and using a lot of plastic.  Contraction could also be a serious problem. You could try to make it in pieces and assemble them or something. But that\'92s expensive.  For this reason I did not explore airfoil shapes much.  I did simulate some and it didn't seem to help much so I didn\'92t pursue it.}
